HEADWORD: Generalizable
<hw>Gen"er*al*i`za*ble</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Capable of
being generalized, or reduced to a general form of statement, or brought
under a general rule.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Extreme cases are . . . not <qex>generalizable</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Coleridge</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Generalization</ent>⟦br⟧
